caption: Watch out when you are ordering pizza and wings online. Store workers will call you back and tell you they don't have wings and charge you only for the pizza for the same price. When you call in to ask why you are being charged the full price for just the pizza the workers will tell you in their system it's showing a different amount so they can't do anything about it. I asked to talk to someone else and morning manager Chad tells me with an attitude that next manager will be in at 1pm and she will tell me the exact same thing. Bunch of crooks over some imaginary wings. Shady business!!!!

I love love love this location! I order from here at least 2 times a week. Lani is the manager I think (she's short, local and kind). She's always kind and attentive to my needs and gives me a warm smile.  I typically order to 10 inch cheese sticks pizza special online for $7 USD and leave her and her team of $5-10 dollars for their service.  My business partner always tells me to tip well wherever I go, so I do. Anyways I do feel the aloha everytime I enter their store and that's why I return time and time again.
When they pick up the phone
Best pizza on the planet. I love Papa John's. My wife and I were in Thailand for a month and I said when we get home the first thing we would do is get a papa John's pizza... Mmmm so good!

Debbie K.  Papa John's Pizza always hot and fresh. I call to order and go pick it up. My order always ready and waiting for me. I like the Hand Tossed Vegetarian Pizza. Their Brownies is onolicious. The workers are always friendly. Excellent customer service.

Craig K.  Papa John's pizzas are good. I like the thin crust Pepperoni. Hand Tossed Meat Lovers and Veggietarian. The Brownies is good. Delicious chocolate flavor. The toppings are always fresh. Pizzas fresh and hot.
Fast and fresh

I wish Google allowed me to give zero stars to this branch. It has happened twice that I order a pizza waited for 45 mins and then doordash peeps call me and then update could not deliver. When I call back to this branch the folks working there have no consideration of the wait there customers do and simply reply that they can place another order which will take another 20 mins to deliver. My place is literally 5 mins walking from there's but still no resolution and consideration .  If you ask for a manager , they say 'I AM THE MANAGER ' . Customer is helpless then and have no option to just cancel the order .  This has happened to me twice now . Very rude and pathetic service .
(Translated by Google) What the Pope's Best  (Original) Ono Papa's Best
The quality and taste of the pieces that was the same and very reliable.   it's always a good to me.

Customer service needs a lot of improvement. I am at the counter for 10 minutes waiting to be helped and the csr guy looks up and says be right with you i wait a little longer and another guys enters and stands to the side of me, we wait about 5 more minutes and the guy looks up again saying be right there. He finally comes and ask the guy behind me" can i help you?" Thankfully the other customer stated" i just need to change my order but (nodding towards me) she was here first."We should have left then but my kids already were excited for pizza so I just went ahead and ordered. After waiting 30-40 minutes for my order the guy just throws it on the counter and walks away not even giving us our soda or instructing us to grab it out of the cooler.  Needless to say we will be sticking to Dominos or Pizza Hut for now on.

I order a pizza Sunday night ! I live close to the store and never come I only receive and apologize? Offer me send the pizza for free 1:20 later? You don’t offer that just send I never order again from Nuuanu store and I live in Nuuanu prefer order and pick up JJ Dolan’s

I order here about twice a week but never had a driver like Michael..he was awesome..made sure we had everything we need and very polite when he dropped our food off at the executive center..i  hope they hire more drivers like him..
Good specials, fast service, delicious food, friendly servers, free parking, close by.
Person on the phone talked WAY  too fast to understand what the pizza choices were since I chose a pizza from the online menu that they don't make anymore..smh!!

I tried to place an online order for a special 3 topping large for $10. A 20TH ANNIVERSARY SPECIAL!!!! The order couldn't go through online so I call it in. Of course you can only get the deal online. What a scam. What's the difference. I understand trying to drive traffic through the system and the efficiency to expedite orders, but I think this is poor customer service. Bait the customer in. My kids wanted Papa John's so I couldn't go back to them and cancel just because of a few bucks. But I don't appreciate the gesture. So I guess the delivery person will collect whatever they get on the other scam, the "delivery charge."  Why not just offer the pizza all inclusive and call it a day! Geeeezz!

Slow service, but good pizza!

Poor customer service.  Entering the restaurant I waited a while for 3 guys to end their joking with each other behind the counter.  I ordered and was told it would be 15 minutes.  After 35 minutes I asked for the status of my order.  They said it would be another few minutes - no apology or explanation.  I waited another 5 minutes and was going to ask for my money back when they gave me my order - again, no apology or explanation.  Never going back to the Nuuanu location.

Top notch ingredients on every pizza I ordered. Literally ate there every day for a week it was so good. I enjoyed the environment and the food so much that I applied and I be never been happier.

I have always ordered from Papa John's nuuanu, but never again...I called to place an order and they put me on hold for 30 mins.  Tried calling a second time and no one answered.  So, I called the one on Kapiolani but was told they don't service my area.  So, I will never purchase nor eat a pizza from Papa John's ever again.

I ordered a medium half all meat, half mushroom and olive, extra sauce and cheese over all and a 20pc bbq wings. I received an all meat pizza with a few olives on half and 2 mushroom slices. Sauce was good. If it had extra cheese, what i got didnt even look like their online pictures. Had a communication problem with woman taking order. Not unusual in Hawaii, but she spoke perfect English and so do I, she just didnt seem to understand the order and i had to repeat my order several times.  She finally read it back to me correctly, but it was entered wrong on the box and the pizza was not what i ordered at all. Long day and to tired to call and complain. I just picked meats off my side. Delivery guy was training. Nice guy, good personality. Gave him $10 tip on top of $50 order. Overall, very disappointed, going back to Dominos. Not only do they get my order right, but they usually suggest ways to keep cost down.
THERE IS NO BETTER PIZZA than PAPA JOHN's, and the fine, hardworking, friendly & did I say REALLY hardworking folks at the NUUANU store are exceptional.
